The paper deals with video representation and classification using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of temporal encoding and feature interactions also suggests a possible fit in multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the end-to-end learning approach, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
